{
  "userId": "uuid/objectId",
  "goal": "Lose Weight | Build Muscle | Maintain",
  "preferences": ["Vegetarian","Low Carb"],
  "availabilityPerWeek": 3,
  "dietaryRestrictions": ["Gluten-free"],
  "updatedAt": "ISO-8601"
}



Endpoints (REST)

POST /api/profile – create first-time profile

Body: goal, preferences[], availabilityPerWeek, dietaryRestrictions[]

Returns: 201 + profile

GET /api/profile/me – read my profile (auth required)

Returns: 200 + profile (or 404 if not created)

PUT /api/profile – update profile (any field)

Returns: 200 + updated profile

(optional) POST /api/profile/replan – regenerate plan on demand (if you want a separate trigger)

Validation (server-side)

goal in enum; availabilityPerWeek int 1–7; arrays length ≤ reasonable bounds.

Return 400 with clear messages (used later by QA).
